Task: Generate Synthetic E-commerce Data (5 Files)

Instructions:


Generate 5 separate CSV files of synthetic e-commerce data.


Each file should represent a different aspect of an e-commerce system:

Customers
Products
Orders
Order Items
Payments



For each file:

Include at least 100 rows of sample data.
Use realistic, varied values typical for e-commerce platforms.
Use English names, addresses, and product information.
Ensure all relationships between files are consistent (e.g., Order Items reference valid Orders and Products).



File Specifications:

Customers.csv

Columns: CustomerID, FirstName, LastName, Email, Phone, Address, City, State, Country, SignupDate


Products.csv

Columns: ProductID, ProductName, Category, Price, StockQuantity, Description


Orders.csv

Columns: OrderID, CustomerID, OrderDate, OrderStatus, ShippingAddress, TotalAmount


OrderItems.csv

Columns: OrderItemID, OrderID, ProductID, Quantity, UnitPrice, Subtotal


Payments.csv

Columns: PaymentID, OrderID, PaymentDate, PaymentAmount, PaymentMethod, PaymentStatus





Output Format:


For each file, provide the CSV data enclosed within triple backticks labeled with the filename.


Example:
Customers.csv
CustomerID,FirstName,LastName,Email,Phone,Address,City,State,Country,SignupDate
1,John,Doe,john.doe@email.com,555-1234,123 Main St,Springfield,IL,USA,2022-01-15
...





Constraints:

Do not include file explanations or any text outside the CSV code blocks.
Ensure all IDs are unique and consistently referenced between files.




Example for Customers.csv (first 2 rows):
Customers.csv
CustomerID,FirstName,LastName,Email,Phone,Address,City,State,Country,SignupDate
1,Jane,Smith,jane.smith@email.com,555-6789,456 Oak Ave,Riverside,CA,USA,2023-03-02
2,Alex,Johnson,alex.j@email.com,555-4321,789 Pine Rd,Greenville,NY,USA,2022-11-19
